  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors have been assessed; the Equivalency of input parameters factor is recorded as not-assessed on the basis that the assessment team judged it inapplicable to a purely computational COU with no physical test article — however, the correct encoding for that determination would be factorStatus 'not-applicable', not 'not-assessed'. At MRL 3 the omission materially weakens the credibility argument.",
