      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties assigned with documented uncertainty ranges; Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainty performed.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 1000 samples across inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity distributions. Input uncertainty characterised at required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental hemolysis measurements from at least three independent test runs per operating point; sample variability reported.",
      "rationale": "Five independent test runs performed per operating point using fresh ovine blood within hematocrit tolerance. Inter-run CV below 8% at all points. Sample adequacy confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that simulation input parameters are equivalent to those used in the physical validation experiment, including geometric tolerances and fluid property matching.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that this factor does not apply to the current COU because the simulation is the primary design tool and no separate physical test article was manufactured for this submission; equivalency of input parameters was therefore considered irrelevant. Accordingly, no assessment activities were scoped or executed. Note: the appropriate encoding for a factor judged inapplicable would be factorStatus 'not-applicable'; the use of 'not-assessed' here is an encoding error that leaves the factor's disposition unverified at Model Risk Level 3."
    }
